===Usage notes===
This character is not to be confused with visually similar but unrelated <span style="font-size:xx-large;" lang=zh>{{l|mul|市}}</span> (<code>U+5E02</code>) ("[[market]]; [[trade]]; [[city]]") which has five strokes and is written <span style="font-size:large;" lang=zh>{{l|mul|亠}}</span> across the top of {{l|mul|巾}}. Note that the {{w|Ming (typefaces)|Ming typeface}} used in Japan and Korea as well as the {{w|Kangxi dictionary}} uses a vertical dot instead of a slanting {{l|mul|丶}} dot for the top component of <span style="font-size:xx-large;" lang=zh>{{l|mul|市}}</span> (<code>U+5E02</code>, 5 strokes) and may appear to be similar with <span style="font-size:xx-large" lang=zh>{{l|mul|巿}}</span> (<code>U+5DFF</code>, 4 strokes) depending on the font used.

